# Data Visualization on Dataset for Data Analytics
## Project Overview
This project focuses on visualizing a cleaned dataset using various graphical techniques to identify trends, patterns, relationships, and outliers. Data visualization helps transform raw data into meaningful insights that support business analysis and decision-making.
## Objectives
* Analyze sales trends and customer behavior
* Evaluate product performance and revenue contribution
* Identify patterns and relationships within the dataset
* Detect outliers through visual analysis
* Communicate insights effectively using charts and graphs
## Tools Used
* Python
* Pandas
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Jupyter Notebook
* Microsoft Excel
## Dataset Information
* Dataset Name: Cleaned Dataset for Data Analytics
* File Format: Excel (.xlsx)
* Domain: Data Analytics
## Data Visualization Tasks Performed
### Order Status Distribution
* Visualized different order statuses
* Identified the most common order status

### Payment Method Usage

* Analyzed payment method frequency
* Identified the most preferred payment method

### Top Selling Products

* Compared product sales quantities
* Identified best-selling products

### Revenue by Product

* Analyzed revenue generated by each product
* Identified products with highest revenue contribution

### Monthly Sales Trend

* Examined monthly revenue patterns
* Identified sales fluctuations and trends

### Referral Source Analysis

* Analyzed customer referral sources
* Identified channels generating the most orders

### Coupon Code Usage

* Visualized coupon code utilization
* Compared popularity of coupon codes

### Quantity vs Total Price Analysis

* Examined relationship between quantity purchased and total price
* Identified possible correlations

### Correlation Heatmap

* Analyzed relationships among numerical variables
* Identified positive and negative correlations

### Total Price Distribution (Box Plot)

* Detected potential outliers
* Examined transaction value distribution

## Results

* Successfully visualized sales and customer behavior patterns
* Identified product performance and revenue contribution
* Analyzed payment preferences and referral effectiveness
* Discovered relationships among numerical variables
* Detected outliers through box plot analysis

## Key Insights

* Order status distribution highlighted variations in completed, pending, and cancelled orders
* Customer payment preferences were identified
* Certain products contributed significantly to sales and revenue
* Monthly sales trends showed revenue fluctuations over time
* Referral source analysis revealed effective customer acquisition channels
* A positive relationship was observed between quantity and total price
* Outliers were identified in transaction values

## Conclusion

The Data Visualization project successfully transformed raw data into meaningful graphical representations. Various charts and plots provided valuable insights into customer behavior, product performance, sales trends, referral effectiveness, and relationships among variables.

